  "informal_statement": "If n < m then 2^n < 2^m -- powers of 2 are strictly increasing in the exponent.",
  "informal_proof_idea": "Show the function k -> 2^k is StrictMono via strictMono_nat_of_lt_succ, which reduces to the single successor step 2^k < 2^(k+1): rewrite via pow_succ to 2^k < 2^k*2, closed by omega given 2^k > 0. Apply the resulting StrictMono fact to the hypothesis n < m.",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem two_pow_strictMono (n m : ℕ) (h : n < m) : 2 ^ n < 2 ^ m",
