  "notes": "Proof authority: Lean kernel via the tracked proof-search loop (episode 9416dbd4), kernel_verified on the third attempt. Fills this domain's weakest-covered focus item, monotonicity (previously only `sum_range_monotone`/`prod_range_monotone`), while also touching `powers`. First attempt used `Nat.pos_pow_of_pos`, which doesn't exist under that name (fixed with the general `pow_pos`). Second attempt's real lesson: after `obtain ⟨k, hk⟩ := Nat.exists_eq_add_of_lt h; subst hk`, the goal became `2^n < 2^(n+k+1)`, and `rw [pow_add]` split off the WRONG grouping -- since `n+k+1` parses left-associatively as `(n+k)+1`, `pow_add` rewrote it as `2^(n+k) * 2^1`, not the intended `2^n * 2^(k+1)` -- producing an unprovable goal shape. Sidestepped entirely by using `strictMono_nat_of_lt_succ` (reduces the claim to a single succ-step `2^k < 2^(k+1)`, cleanly matched by `pow_succ` with no exponent-splitting ambiguity) instead of manually decomposing `m` via `exists_eq_add_of_lt`.",
